[0.008013, "o", "Ubuntu Server 24.04.4 LTS (live-server) — signed (Canonical CA)\r\n\r\n  Slug:        ubuntu-24.04-live-server\r\n  Architecture: x86_64\r\n  Approx size:  2.5 GiB (2600 MiB)\r\n  Purpose:      Ubuntu LTS server installer. Validated under aegis-boot v0.12.0 #109.\r\n\r\n  ISO URL:      https://releases.ubuntu.com/24.04/ubuntu-24.04.4-live-server-amd64.iso\r\n  SHA256SUMS:   https://releases.ubuntu.com/24.04/SHA256SUMS\r\n  Signature:    https://releases.ubuntu.com/24.04/SHA256SUMS.gpg\r\n\r\nManual download + verify + add (Linux host):\r\n\r\n  curl -LO 'https://releases.ubuntu.com/24.04/ubuntu-24.04.4-live-server-amd64.iso'\r\n  curl -LO 'https://releases.ubuntu.com/24.04/SHA256SUMS'\r\n  curl -LO 'https://releases.ubuntu.com/24.04/SHA256SUMS.gpg'\r\n\r\n  # Verify the SHA256SUMS file's signature using the project's\r\n  # signing key (consult the project for key fingerprint), then:\r\n  sha256sum -c <SHA256SUMS> --ignore-missing\r\n  aegis-boot add <iso-filename>\r\n\r\nOnce verified + on the stick, the rescue-tui will show this ISO with the\r\nverification verdict. Tracked in epic #136 for future `aegis-boot fetch <slug>`\r\nwhich will automate the manual recipe above.\r\n"]
